01:28:15.600 --> 01:28:19.920
This is a checkup for ‘this’,&nbsp;
‘that’, ‘these’, ‘those’,

01:28:20.720 --> 01:28:24.080
possessive adjectives, and possessive pronouns.

01:28:24.640 --> 01:28:25.360
Okay.

01:28:25.360 --> 01:28:31.600
Now here, I want you to focus on ‘this’,
‘that’, ‘these’, and ‘those’.

01:28:32.240 --> 01:28:34.960
Okay, so here’s the first example.

01:28:35.760 --> 01:28:36.960
We have a dog.

01:28:37.760 --> 01:28:38.480
One dog.

01:28:39.120 --> 01:28:43.440
So we have to use ‘this’ or ‘that’.

01:28:43.440 --> 01:28:44.160
Okay.

01:28:44.160 --> 01:28:48.240
If it’s close, I say, “This is a dog.”

01:28:48.880 --> 01:28:53.440
If it’s far away, I say, “That is a dog.”

01:28:54.320 --> 01:28:57.440
So, I’m going to write ‘this’.

01:28:58.720 --> 01:28:59.040
Okay.

01:28:59.760 --> 01:29:03.040
The next one says, “…are balloons.”

01:29:04.000 --> 01:29:06.480
“…are balloons.” With an ‘s’.

01:29:07.040 --> 01:29:08.320
There’s more than one.

01:29:08.880 --> 01:29:11.440
So can we use ‘this’ or ‘that’?

01:29:12.240 --> 01:29:12.480
No.

01:29:13.120 --> 01:29:16.080
We have to use ‘these’ or ‘those’.

01:29:16.800 --> 01:29:21.280
So, if it’s close, I say “These are balloons.”

01:29:22.320 --> 01:29:26.000
If they are far, “Those are balloons.”

01:29:26.640 --> 01:29:27.440
Okay.

01:29:27.440 --> 01:29:31.200
So let’s write ‘those’.

01:29:31.760 --> 01:29:33.440
“Those are balloons.”

01:29:34.560 --> 01:29:35.280
Okay.

01:29:35.280 --> 01:29:38.080
Now when we ask the question,

01:29:38.080 --> 01:29:39.840
“Are these pens?”

01:29:40.960 --> 01:29:42.640
we have more than one.

01:29:43.360 --> 01:29:46.160
“These pens.” With an ‘s’.

01:29:46.960 --> 01:29:47.360
Okay.

01:29:47.920 --> 01:29:50.320
I can put two answers here.

01:29:51.040 --> 01:29:53.360
“No, ___ aren’t.”

01:29:59.360 --> 01:30:00.946
I can say “No, these aren’t.”

01:30:00.946 --> 01:30:05.840
Or… I can say “No, they..."&nbsp;
more than one "... they aren’t.”

01:30:07.760 --> 01:30:08.080
Okay.

01:30:08.800 --> 01:30:12.960
The next one. “These ____ eyes.”

01:30:13.760 --> 01:30:15.520
We need a ‘be’ verb.

01:30:16.160 --> 01:30:16.480
Okay.

01:30:17.600 --> 01:30:19.120
There’s more than one, right.

01:30:19.120 --> 01:30:20.400
There are two eyes.

01:30:20.960 --> 01:30:24.960
So, “These are eyes.”

01:30:25.920 --> 01:30:26.880
Okay.

01:30:26.880 --> 01:30:29.440
And here “…is a nose.”

01:30:30.400 --> 01:30:30.720
One.

01:30:32.000 --> 01:30:32.800
A nose.

01:30:32.800 --> 01:30:33.840
And it’s close.

01:30:34.480 --> 01:30:39.760
So, I have to say, “This is a nose.”

01:30:40.480 --> 01:30:42.720
Okay, let’s move on to the next part.

01:30:44.160 --> 01:30:46.560
We’re going to do some more checkup.

01:30:46.560 --> 01:30:52.560
Now here, I want you to focus on possessive
adjectives and possessive pronouns.

01:30:53.120 --> 01:30:54.880
Let’s look at the first example.

01:30:55.760 --> 01:30:57.840
“These are my pen.”

01:30:58.960 --> 01:30:59.440
Okay.

01:31:00.160 --> 01:31:03.360
We have ‘these…are’.

01:31:04.640 --> 01:31:07.280
This means we need more than one.

01:31:07.280 --> 01:31:08.000
Right…

01:31:08.000 --> 01:31:09.200
More than one pen.

01:31:09.760 --> 01:31:11.760
So, we have to put ‘s’.

01:31:12.480 --> 01:31:14.480
“These are my pens.”

01:31:15.360 --> 01:31:16.320
Okay.

01:31:16.320 --> 01:31:18.400
Let’s look at these two together.

01:31:19.360 --> 01:31:22.160
“Those aren’t her children.”

01:31:23.680 --> 01:31:24.560
Okay.

01:31:24.560 --> 01:31:28.760
So we can also say, “Those aren’t ____.”

01:31:29.280 --> 01:31:30.440
What do we put?

01:31:30.440 --> 01:31:32.400
“… her children.”

01:31:33.200 --> 01:31:36.960
We can always say, “Those aren’t hers.”

01:31:37.600 --> 01:31:38.560
Okay.

01:31:38.560 --> 01:31:40.480
We don’t need a noun here.

01:31:41.040 --> 01:31:44.160
We do need a noun over here, though.

01:31:44.160 --> 01:31:44.640
Okay.

01:31:45.600 --> 01:31:47.760
Then, “Is it yours?”

01:31:48.880 --> 01:31:49.680
“Is it yours?”

01:31:50.560 --> 01:31:52.680
“Yes, it’s _____.”

01:31:53.200 --> 01:31:54.480
There’s no noun.

01:31:54.480 --> 01:31:57.840
We have to say…

01:31:58.720 --> 01:31:59.200
“mine”.

01:32:00.000 --> 01:32:00.800
“Is it yours?”

01:32:01.440 --> 01:32:02.720
“Yes, it’s mine.”

01:32:03.920 --> 01:32:04.720
Okay.

01:32:04.720 --> 01:32:05.760
And the last two…

01:32:05.760 --> 01:32:09.520
” _____ these his shoes?”

01:32:10.640 --> 01:32:12.480
We need a ‘be’ verb here.

01:32:12.480 --> 01:32:14.800
” _____ these his shoes?”

01:32:15.520 --> 01:32:19.680
We have ‘these’, and we have ‘shoes’ with an ‘s’.

01:32:19.680 --> 01:32:22.400
So we need the plural ‘be’ verb.

01:32:24.720 --> 01:32:27.280
“Are”.
“Are these his shoes?”

01:32:28.080 --> 01:32:28.800
Okay.

01:32:28.800 --> 01:32:31.200
And the answer. “No, they…”

01:32:32.560 --> 01:32:33.040
Plural.

01:32:34.720 --> 01:32:34.960
“…are.”

01:32:35.920 --> 01:32:39.840
We have ‘no’. “No, they aren’t”

01:32:40.800 --> 01:32:41.360
Okay.

01:32:41.360 --> 01:32:42.640
“Are not, aren’t”.

01:32:43.360 --> 01:32:44.000
Okay.

01:32:44.000 --> 01:32:45.760
Let’s move on to the next part.

01:32:47.120 --> 01:32:50.560
For this last part, we’re going to look
at these sentences.

01:32:51.200 --> 01:32:53.440
But they’re all wrong.

01:32:53.440 --> 01:32:55.440
They all have mistakes.

01:32:55.440 --> 01:32:58.560
So you have to find the mistakes for me.

01:32:59.360 --> 01:33:00.240
Okay.

01:33:00.240 --> 01:33:04.080
So, the first one says, “That are chairs.”

01:33:04.600 --> 01:33:06.720
Hmmmm, we know that’s wrong.

01:33:07.520 --> 01:33:11.120
‘That’ is used for singular nouns.

01:33:11.120 --> 01:33:11.440
One.

01:33:12.320 --> 01:33:17.280
But it says “are” and it says “chairs”
with an ‘s’.

01:33:18.000 --> 01:33:22.320
So, we have to change this word.

01:33:22.320 --> 01:33:27.120
We can say, “These are chairs.”

01:33:27.120 --> 01:33:29.360
or “Those are chairs.”

01:33:30.320 --> 01:33:30.800
Okay.

01:33:31.600 --> 01:33:33.440
“This book is my.”

01:33:34.600 --> 01:33:35.600
Hmm.

01:33:35.600 --> 01:33:38.080
We have the possessive pronoun ‘my’.

01:33:38.960 --> 01:33:42.960
But remember, you have to have a noun after,

01:33:42.960 --> 01:33:44.400
but there’s no noun.

01:33:45.280 --> 01:33:51.440
So, we can change this to the&nbsp;
possessive adjective ‘mine’.

01:33:52.160 --> 01:33:52.880
Okay.

01:33:52.880 --> 01:33:55.840
You don’t need a noun if you say ‘mine’.

01:33:57.360 --> 01:33:57.760
Okay.

01:33:58.480 --> 01:34:00.640
“That is he house.”

01:34:02.120 --> 01:34:03.120
Hmm.

01:34:03.120 --> 01:34:09.280
We want to show that this house belongs to
this man or boy.

01:34:09.280 --> 01:34:10.800
“That is he house.”

01:34:11.440 --> 01:34:15.600
But this word ‘he’, does not show possession.

01:34:17.200 --> 01:34:18.000
Okay.

01:34:18.000 --> 01:34:22.080
So, we say, “This is his house.”

01:34:22.800 --> 01:34:25.280
‘His’, then the noun ‘house’.

01:34:27.360 --> 01:34:29.360
Similarly, for the next one.

01:34:29.920 --> 01:34:31.840
“She name is Jenny.”

01:34:32.880 --> 01:34:36.880
We want to show that this name belongs to Jenny.

01:34:37.680 --> 01:34:38.880
So, we say…

01:34:41.200 --> 01:34:41.440
“her”.

01:34:42.640 --> 01:34:45.920
“Her name is Jenny.”

01:34:45.920 --> 01:34:48.880
Okay, and the last one is also similar.

01:34:49.520 --> 01:34:51.440
“It’s ours house.”

01:34:52.560 --> 01:34:55.840
Now, if we don’t have ‘house’, “It’s ours.”

01:34:56.400 --> 01:34:57.920
We can say that.

01:34:57.920 --> 01:35:01.440
But since we have a noun, …

01:35:01.440 --> 01:35:04.240
we use the possessive pronoun,

01:35:04.240 --> 01:35:06.000
“It’s ‘our’ house.”

01:35:06.880 --> 01:35:07.760
Okay.

01:35:07.760 --> 01:35:12.960
That was the checkup for possessive&nbsp;
pronouns, possessive adjectives,

01:35:12.960 --> 01:35:15.360
‘this’, ‘that’, ‘these’, and ‘those’.

01:35:15.360 --> 01:35:18.560
I hope you understood, and I’ll see you
in the next video.

01:35:18.560 --> 01:35:28.240
Bye.

