01:35:29.680 --> 01:35:36.000
In this video, we’re going to talk about
the articles; ‘a’, ‘an’ and ‘the’.

01:35:36.880 --> 01:35:42.240
Now this can be very confusing, so please
make sure you pay careful attention.

01:35:43.200 --> 01:35:46.880
We use articles in front of nouns.

01:35:46.880 --> 01:35:50.000
Okay, so remember that and&nbsp;
let’s look at the board.

01:35:51.440 --> 01:35:57.280
First, we use ‘a’ or ‘an’ when we’re
talking about any one thing.

01:35:58.320 --> 01:36:04.240
For example, let’s say I&nbsp;
say, “A banana is delicious.”

01:36:04.240 --> 01:36:06.800
Okay, that means all bananas.

01:36:06.800 --> 01:36:09.840
Any banana is delicious.

01:36:09.840 --> 01:36:12.080
“A banana is delicious.”

01:36:12.800 --> 01:36:15.360
Okay, let’s jump over here.

01:36:15.360 --> 01:36:18.560
If I’m talking about a specific banana…

01:36:18.560 --> 01:36:20.640
maybe I have a banana in my hand.

01:36:21.440 --> 01:36:24.560
It’s specific, not any banana, this one.

01:36:25.520 --> 01:36:27.120
I have to use ‘the’,

01:36:28.240 --> 01:36:30.400
“The banana is old.”

01:36:31.440 --> 01:36:32.800
Okay. This one.

01:36:33.600 --> 01:36:37.040
I can’t say, “A banana is old.”

01:36:37.040 --> 01:36:39.760
Then that means all bananas are old.

01:36:39.760 --> 01:36:42.720
And that’s not true. Just this one.

01:36:42.720 --> 01:36:45.520
So, I say, “The banana is old.”

01:36:46.480 --> 01:36:48.320
Okay, let’s move over here.

01:36:48.880 --> 01:36:54.800
We also use ‘a’ or ‘an’ when we’re
talking about something for the first time.

01:36:55.840 --> 01:36:57.760
So, I have another example here.

01:36:58.320 --> 01:37:00.400
“I watched a movie.”

01:37:01.040 --> 01:37:01.840
Okay.

01:37:01.840 --> 01:37:08.480
I’m talking about this movie for the first
time, so I have to use “…a movie”.

01:37:09.920 --> 01:37:13.280
But, if I want to talk about this movie again,

01:37:13.280 --> 01:37:17.840
for the second time, or the&nbsp;
third time or fourth, fifth…

01:37:17.840 --> 01:37:18.720
it doesn’t matter.

01:37:19.280 --> 01:37:20.960
I have to use ‘the’.

01:37:22.160 --> 01:37:24.400
“The movie was fun.”

01:37:25.040 --> 01:37:27.520
I’m talking about this one. The specific.

01:37:28.240 --> 01:37:30.240
“The movie was fun.”

01:37:31.280 --> 01:37:34.400
I can’t say, “A movie was fun.”

01:37:34.400 --> 01:37:36.480
That means all movies are fun.

01:37:36.480 --> 01:37:37.280
That’s not true.

01:37:38.080 --> 01:37:39.760
“The movie was fun.”

01:37:41.200 --> 01:37:43.920
Okay, and I also use ‘the’

01:37:43.920 --> 01:37:47.840
when I’m talking about a noun&nbsp;
where there’s only one and only.

01:37:48.480 --> 01:37:49.280
Okay.

01:37:49.280 --> 01:37:52.720
For example, there’s only one sun.

01:37:52.720 --> 01:37:56.320
Okay, when I look at the&nbsp;
sky, there’s only one sun.

01:37:56.320 --> 01:37:58.160
So, I say, “The sun.”

01:37:59.040 --> 01:38:00.720
“The sun is hot.”

01:38:00.720 --> 01:38:02.960
I cannot say, “A sun.”

01:38:02.960 --> 01:38:04.160
That’s wrong.

01:38:04.160 --> 01:38:07.600
When there’s one and only, we say, “The sun.”

01:38:08.320 --> 01:38:08.960
Okay.

01:38:08.960 --> 01:38:10.560
Let’s look at some more examples.

01:38:11.520 --> 01:38:15.840
The first example says, “A lion is dangerous.”

01:38:16.640 --> 01:38:21.600
I have to use ‘a’ because I’m&nbsp;
talking about any one lion.

01:38:21.600 --> 01:38:23.440
Any lion is dangerous.

01:38:24.000 --> 01:38:26.320
All lions are dangerous.

01:38:26.320 --> 01:38:27.840
So, I use ‘a’.

01:38:29.040 --> 01:38:32.240
The next sentence says, “It’s a dog.”

01:38:33.200 --> 01:38:39.280
I’m talking about this dog for the first time,
so I use ‘a’.

01:38:40.720 --> 01:38:45.120
Now, I’m talking about this&nbsp;
dog for the second time.

01:38:45.120 --> 01:38:48.560
So, I say, “The dog is cute.”

01:38:49.760 --> 01:38:50.400
Okay.

01:38:50.400 --> 01:38:52.240
Here’s a similar example.

01:38:52.880 --> 01:38:54.080
“It’s an ant.”

01:38:55.040 --> 01:39:00.400
Well, I used ‘an’ because we have ‘ant’,
which start with a vowel.

01:39:00.400 --> 01:39:04.160
And I’m talking about this ant for the first
time.

01:39:05.120 --> 01:39:06.240
“It’s an ant.”

01:39:07.120 --> 01:39:09.920
Now, I’m talking about this ant again.

01:39:10.800 --> 01:39:12.800
“The ant is small.”

01:39:14.080 --> 01:39:16.960
“The ant…”, this one, “…is small.”

01:39:18.240 --> 01:39:20.000
Okay, and the last one.

01:39:20.000 --> 01:39:21.440
“It’s the moon.”

01:39:22.160 --> 01:39:26.320
I have to say, “the moon”&nbsp;
because there’s only one moon.

01:39:27.360 --> 01:39:29.120
I cannot say, “a moon”.

01:39:30.560 --> 01:39:31.600
“It’s the moon.

01:39:32.240 --> 01:39:36.000
The moon…”, only one, “…is round.”

01:39:37.200 --> 01:39:37.840
Okay.

01:39:37.840 --> 01:39:39.840
Let’s look at some more examples.

01:39:42.000 --> 01:39:44.480
Okay, we have some more examples,

01:39:44.480 --> 01:39:50.800
but this time I want you to think about&nbsp;
whether we should put ‘a’, ‘an’ or ‘the’.

01:39:51.760 --> 01:39:52.240
Okay.

01:39:52.800 --> 01:39:56.480
So, “I see ____ desk and ___ chair.”

01:39:57.600 --> 01:40:00.720
We don’t know which desk and chair.

01:40:00.720 --> 01:40:03.920
And it’s the first time I’m talking about them.

01:40:04.480 --> 01:40:07.840
So, we have to put ‘a’.

01:40:08.800 --> 01:40:13.040
“I see a desk and a chair.”

01:40:14.560 --> 01:40:15.680
The next one.

01:40:15.680 --> 01:40:17.600
“I see ____ octopus.”

01:40:18.160 --> 01:40:20.480
Okay, this is the same.

01:40:20.480 --> 01:40:24.560
It’s the first time I’m&nbsp;
talking about this octopus.

01:40:25.120 --> 01:40:27.680
So, do I put ‘a’ or ‘an’?

01:40:28.720 --> 01:40:31.120
Well here we have the vowel ‘o’.

01:40:31.760 --> 01:40:34.720
So we have to put “‘an’ octopus”.

01:40:35.360 --> 01:40:37.440
“I see an octopus.”

01:40:38.560 --> 01:40:40.640
Okay, the next one.

01:40:40.640 --> 01:40:41.680
“It’s ___ pen.”

01:40:42.640 --> 01:40:44.240
Okay, it’s the same.

01:40:44.240 --> 01:40:47.280
It’s the first time, so I say, “a pen”.

01:40:48.400 --> 01:40:51.920
Now, I’m talking about the&nbsp;
pen for the second time.

01:40:52.640 --> 01:40:57.840
So I say, “The pen is red.”

01:40:58.560 --> 01:41:00.640
Okay, I’m talking about this one.

01:41:00.640 --> 01:41:01.600
So I say, “the”.

01:41:02.560 --> 01:41:04.320
Okay, similarly…

01:41:04.320 --> 01:41:06.320
“She is ____ girl.”

01:41:07.200 --> 01:41:08.080
What do I say?

01:41:09.760 --> 01:41:10.880
“a girl.”

01:41:10.880 --> 01:41:13.440
We’re talking about her for the first time.

01:41:14.240 --> 01:41:14.720
Okay.

01:41:14.720 --> 01:41:19.120
And now we’re talking about this girl again,
