In this video, we’re going to learn how
to ask questions using ‘have’.

02:08:01.520 --> 02:08:03.120
Okay, let’s look at the board.

02:08:04.800 --> 02:08:08.480
When we are talking about ‘he’, ‘she’ or ‘it’,

02:08:09.040 --> 02:08:11.600
the question always begins with ‘does’.

02:08:13.280 --> 02:08:15.200
After the pronoun, we have ‘have’.

02:08:15.920 --> 02:08:18.080
So, we say, “Does he have…”

02:08:19.120 --> 02:08:20.080
“Does she have…”

02:08:20.960 --> 02:08:21.840
“Does it have…”

02:08:22.960 --> 02:08:27.680
Now, let’s practice with this question and
let’s look at the two answers.

02:08:28.400 --> 02:08:29.200
Okay.

02:08:29.200 --> 02:08:30.400
“Does he have a friend?”

02:08:31.840 --> 02:08:34.560
If the answer is ‘yes’, we say “yes”,

02:08:35.520 --> 02:08:39.360
in the blank, we match… this has to be the same.

02:08:40.160 --> 02:08:41.760
“Yes, he does.”

02:08:42.560 --> 02:08:43.840
If the answer is ‘no’.

02:08:44.640 --> 02:08:46.320
“No, he doesn’t.”

02:08:47.200 --> 02:08:48.640
“Does he have a friend?”

02:08:49.840 --> 02:08:51.200
“Yes, she does.”

02:08:52.400 --> 02:08:54.000
“No, she doesn’t.”

02:08:55.360 --> 02:08:57.120
“Does it have a friend?”

02:08:58.240 --> 02:08:59.920
“Yes, it does.”

02:09:00.800 --> 02:09:02.560
“No, it doesn’t.”

02:09:03.600 --> 02:09:06.000
Okay, so remember ‘does…have’.

02:09:06.880 --> 02:09:13.280
Now, when we use ‘you’, ‘we’, ‘they’,
we use ‘do’ in the front.

02:09:14.160 --> 02:09:15.600
And ‘have’ after.

02:09:16.720 --> 02:09:17.840
“Do you have a friend?”

02:09:19.280 --> 02:09:20.640
“Do we have a friend?”

02:09:21.520 --> 02:09:22.960
“Do they have a friend?”

02:09:24.240 --> 02:09:24.960
Okay.

02:09:24.960 --> 02:09:27.600
And again, we have two answers.

02:09:27.600 --> 02:09:29.680
We finish with ‘do’ or ‘don’t’.

02:09:30.480 --> 02:09:32.320
So, “Do you have a friend?”

02:09:33.360 --> 02:09:35.280
“Yes, I do.”

02:09:35.920 --> 02:09:38.960
Right, the question is asking ‘you’,
so, you say “I do.”

02:09:39.520 --> 02:09:41.360
Or, “No, I don’t.”

02:09:42.560 --> 02:09:44.000
“Do we have a friend?”

02:09:44.960 --> 02:09:46.320
“Yes, we do.”

02:09:47.120 --> 02:09:49.440
Or, “No, we don’t.”

02:09:50.400 --> 02:09:51.440
And last.

02:09:51.440 --> 02:09:52.960
“Do they have a friend?”

02:09:53.920 --> 02:09:55.200
“Yes, they do.”

02:09:56.240 --> 02:09:57.680
“No, they don’t.”

02:09:58.400 --> 02:10:00.920
Okay, let’s move on to some more practice.

