Okay.

02:10:08.640 --> 02:10:10.800
So let’s look at the first practice.

02:10:11.680 --> 02:10:12.880
It’s a question.

02:10:13.600 --> 02:10:19.040
Okay, so remember when we ask a question,
we begin with ‘do’ or ‘does’.

02:10:19.600 --> 02:10:20.320
Okay.

02:10:20.320 --> 02:10:21.280
We have ‘she’.

02:10:22.240 --> 02:10:25.520
Well, remember for all questions we use ‘have’.

02:10:27.040 --> 02:10:29.760
In the front, should we use ‘does’ or ‘do’?

02:10:31.440 --> 02:10:33.040
The answer is ‘does’.

02:10:33.920 --> 02:10:35.680
“Does she have a dress?”

02:10:36.960 --> 02:10:39.040
When we answer, “Yes…”

02:10:40.240 --> 02:10:41.840
What do we put here?

02:10:41.840 --> 02:10:44.560
Remember, we put the pronoun ‘she’.

02:10:45.680 --> 02:10:47.920
And the answer ‘does’.

02:10:49.200 --> 02:10:50.800
“Yes, she does.”

02:10:52.160 --> 02:10:53.040
The next one.

02:10:53.040 --> 02:10:54.080
We have ‘they’.

02:10:55.040 --> 02:10:57.200
Okay, ‘have’ is again the same.

02:10:58.080 --> 02:10:59.200
“…have a bicycle?”

02:10:59.920 --> 02:11:01.840
Okay, what goes in the front?

02:11:02.880 --> 02:11:05.120
For ‘they’, we use ‘do’.

02:11:06.160 --> 02:11:08.320
“Do they have a bicycle?”

02:11:09.680 --> 02:11:12.000
This time the answer is negative.

02:11:12.800 --> 02:11:14.000
“No, they….”

02:11:15.440 --> 02:11:16.480
What do we put here?

