02:27:12.080 --> 02:27:18.399
Remember ‘be’ verbs, in the present simple
tense, can be ‘is’, ‘am’, or ‘are’.

02:27:19.200 --> 02:27:21.519
Take a look at the first sentence.

02:27:21.520 --> 02:27:24.560
It says, ‘She _ blank _ at school.’

