The subject of this sentence is ‘they’.

02:28:02.399 --> 02:28:04.559
What ‘be’ verb do we use for ‘they’?

02:28:05.760 --> 02:28:12.080
The correct answer is ‘are’.

02:28:12.080 --> 02:28:16.640
For the negative, you can also use ‘aren't’
or ‘are not’.

02:28:17.760 --> 02:28:22.720
Also if you want to use the contraction for
‘they are’, you can say,

02:28:22.720 --> 02:28:25.840
‘They're 20 years old.’

